nodes.bodyText: Now these formatting the problem is ArtifactProblem's responsibility.
This is warn because having a unresolvable Maven artifact should not cause the build failure as long as there is no linkage errors.
make this a comment in the code
Should this be a subclass instead? That is, should there be subclasses for different types of artifact problems? Using a type object feels not very object oriented.
Great idea. Removed the type in favor of class hierarchy.
Should SymbolProblem (or whatever it's called) and ArtifactProblem have  a common superclass?
No, I don't see advantage to have a common superclass for SymbolProblem and ArtifactProblem. They do not share any property. They are not handled in a container class (Set or Map) together.
This sounds like a run on sentence.

nodes.bodyText: All these static methods could be constructors in subclasses.
This switch strongly suggests this class really does need multiple subclasses.
The Type enum is removed in favor of InvalidClassFileProblem and UnresolvableArtifactProblem. They don't have switch statement.
